    <fo:block text-indent='.333in' font-size='12pt' space-before='.388in'>The above percentages are computed on per daily basis. 
    Note that the ratios are more divergent than the "5 Days Performance Percentages" presented at the top main report. 
    The daily inaccuracy is the main reason I prefer to use estimates based on averages over an extended period, such as 1-5 Days, 6 - 10 Days, etc.
    </fo:block>
    
    
    <fo:block page-break-before="always" space-before='.388in' font-size='9pt'>Notes:</fo:block>
    <fo:block text-indent='.333in' font-size='6.25pt'>1. Percentage change calculation uses the closing price on the day of the report
    divided into the closing price so many days out.  The abridged report found on the website performs a different calculation. The
    website report uses the closing prices average within the projected period.  This report uses the closing price for the projected day.</fo:block>
    <fo:block text-indent='.333in' font-size='6.25pt'>2. A Buy indicator must have a value greater than 7.00. 
    Prior to 2021-08-26 the value was 6.75. </fo:block>
    <fo:block text-indent='.333in' font-size='6.25pt'>3. A Sell indicator must have a value less than 2.00.
    Prior to 2021-08-26 the sell value was 2.25.  </fo:block>
     
    <fo:block text-indent='.333in' font-size='6.25pt'>4. Category by ETFs Report - </fo:block>
    	<fo:block text-indent='.66in' font-size='6.25pt'>4.1 does not include ETFs labeled with 
	    "inverse" or "bear". </fo:block>
    
    	<fo:block text-indent='.66in' font-size='6.25pt'>4.2 does include leveraged ETFs (aka ETNs); since the
	    report shows a "likeliness" of change and not a predicted percentage change. </fo:block>
      
    <fo:block text-indent='.333in' font-size='6.25pt'>5. The 5, 10, 15, etc. day period moving average functions 
      are based exponential weighted (based on day period).
      </fo:block>

